<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Mutex on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/mutex/</link><description>Recent content in Mutex on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/mutex/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C++ std::mutex try_lock — Mutex Lock Failure Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/mutex-try-lock/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/cpp/mutex-try-lock/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-stdmutex-try_lock--mutex-lock-failure-fix"&gt;[Solution] C++ std::mutex try_lock — Mutex Lock Failure Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;std::mutex::try_lock()&lt;/code&gt; attempts to lock the mutex without blocking — it returns &lt;code&gt;false&lt;/code&gt; if the mutex is already locked. While &lt;code&gt;try_lock&lt;/code&gt; itself does not throw, &lt;code&gt;std::mutex::lock()&lt;/code&gt; throws &lt;code&gt;std::system_error&lt;/code&gt; with &lt;code&gt;resource_deadlock_would_occur&lt;/code&gt; if deadlock is detected, and improper use of try_lock can lead to missed critical sections or livelock.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="why-mutex-lock-failures-occur"&gt;Why Mutex Lock Failures Occur&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common causes include recursive locking without &lt;code&gt;std::recursive_mutex&lt;/code&gt;, deadlock from inconsistent lock ordering across threads, using &lt;code&gt;try_lock&lt;/code&gt; in a busy-wait loop without backoff, and calling &lt;code&gt;lock()&lt;/code&gt; on a mutex that the current thread already holds.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go RWMutex Not Locked Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/sync-mutex-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/sync-mutex-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="rwmutex-not-locked-error-fix"&gt;RWMutex Not Locked Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;sync: RWMutex is not locked&lt;/code&gt; error occurs when trying to unlock a mutex that isn&amp;rsquo;t currently locked, or when calling &lt;code&gt;RUnlock&lt;/code&gt; without a matching &lt;code&gt;RLock&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;sync.RWMutex&lt;/code&gt; allows multiple concurrent readers OR a single writer. The runtime panics if you call &lt;code&gt;Unlock&lt;/code&gt; on a mutex that isn&amp;rsquo;t locked, or &lt;code&gt;RUnlock&lt;/code&gt; without a corresponding &lt;code&gt;RLock&lt;/code&gt;. This is a programming error that indicates incorrect synchronization logic.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Go Sync RWMutex Not Locked Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/sync-mutex/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/go/sync-mutex/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="sync-rwmutex-is-not-locked--fix"&gt;Sync: RWMutex Is Not Locked — Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &amp;ldquo;sync: RWMutex is not locked&amp;rdquo; error occurs when you call &lt;code&gt;RUnlock()&lt;/code&gt; on an &lt;code&gt;RWMutex&lt;/code&gt; that isn&amp;rsquo;t currently held for reading, or &lt;code&gt;Unlock()&lt;/code&gt; on a mutex that isn&amp;rsquo;t locked.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Go&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;sync.RWMutex&lt;/code&gt; enforces locking discipline. Calling &lt;code&gt;RUnlock()&lt;/code&gt; when no read lock is held, or &lt;code&gt;Unlock()&lt;/code&gt; when no write lock is held, causes a runtime panic. This is a safeguard against misusing the mutex.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux ENOTRECOVERABLE (errno 88) — State Not Recoverable Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-88/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-88/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-enotrecoverable-errno-88--state-not-recoverable"&gt;Linux ENOTRECOVERABLE (errno 88) — State Not Recoverable&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ENOTRECOVERABLE (errno 88) means the state protected by a robust mutex cannot be recovered. This error occurs after EOWNERDEAD when the application fails to make the mutex consistent, or when the protected state is irreparably corrupted. It is distinct from EOWNERDEAD (errno 87) because ENOTRECOVERABLE means recovery is impossible, while EOWNERDEAD means recovery can be attempted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Failed to call &lt;code&gt;pthread_mutex_consistent()&lt;/code&gt; after EOWNERDEAD&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Protected data structure was corrupted beyond repair&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Two processes attempted recovery simultaneously&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Application state is irrecoverable after owner death&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-enotrecoverable"&gt;How to Fix ENOTRECOVERABLE&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-destroy-and-reinitialize-the-mutex"&gt;1. Destroy and Reinitialize the Mutex&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The only fix is to reset the mutex:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux EOWNERDEAD (errno 87) — Owner Died Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-87/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/errno-87/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-eownerdead-errno-87--owner-died"&gt;Linux EOWNERDEAD (errno 87) — Owner Died&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EOWNERDEAD (errno 87) means the previous owner of a robust mutex has terminated without releasing the lock. This error occurs when a process that held a &lt;code&gt;PTHREAD_MUTEX_ROBUST&lt;/code&gt; mutex crashes or is killed, and another process tries to acquire the same mutex. It is distinct from EDEADLK (errno 35) because EOWNERDEAD indicates the owner process died, not a deadlock situation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Process holding a robust mutex crashed or was killed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Application terminated without releasing mutex locks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shared memory mutex left in inconsistent state&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Daemon process died while holding a lock&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix-eownerdead"&gt;How to Fix EOWNERDEAD&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-recover-the-mutex-state"&gt;1. Recover the Mutex State&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When EOWNERDEAD is returned, the mutex is now yours but in an inconsistent state. You must mark it consistent:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Mutex Poisoned — Lock Poison Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/unwrap-after-lock-2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/unwrap-after-lock-2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="mutex-poisoned--lock-poison-error"&gt;Mutex Poisoned — Lock Poison Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A panic with the message &amp;ldquo;Mutex is poisoned&amp;rdquo; (or an &lt;code&gt;Err(PoisonError)&lt;/code&gt; from &lt;code&gt;.lock().unwrap()&lt;/code&gt;) occurs when you try to lock a &lt;code&gt;Mutex&lt;/code&gt; that has been poisoned by a thread that panicked while holding the lock.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;Mutex&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; marks itself as &amp;ldquo;poisoned&amp;rdquo; when a thread panics while holding the lock. This is a safety mechanism — the data inside might be in an inconsistent state. By default, &lt;code&gt;.lock().unwrap()&lt;/code&gt; on a poisoned mutex panics again.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Rust Mutex Poisoned — Mutex Lock Poison Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/unwrap-after-lock/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/rust/unwrap-after-lock/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="mutex-poisoned--mutex-lock-poison-error"&gt;Mutex Poisoned — Mutex Lock Poison Error&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A panic with the message &amp;ldquo;Mutex is poisoned&amp;rdquo; occurs when you try to lock a &lt;code&gt;Mutex&lt;/code&gt; that has been poisoned. A mutex becomes poisoned when a thread panics while holding the lock.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust&amp;rsquo;s &lt;code&gt;Mutex&amp;lt;T&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; provides mutual exclusion for shared data. When a thread panics while holding a mutex lock, the mutex is marked as &amp;ldquo;poisoned&amp;rdquo; to prevent potentially inconsistent data from being used by other threads. The idea is that if a thread panicked, the protected data might be in an inconsistent state.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Ruby ThreadError — Thread Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/thread-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/thread-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="threaderror--thread-error-fix"&gt;ThreadError — Thread Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ThreadError&lt;/code&gt; is raised when there&amp;rsquo;s an error with a Thread, such as joining a dead thread, deadlock detection, or mutex issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;ThreadError&lt;/code&gt; covers various thread-related errors in Ruby. This includes deadlock detection, trying to join a thread that&amp;rsquo;s already been joined, and mutex-related issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Common scenarios:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deadlock detected&lt;/strong&gt; — threads waiting on each other.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join dead thread&lt;/strong&gt; — trying to join a thread that has finished.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mutex not locked&lt;/strong&gt; — trying to unlock a mutex that isn&amp;rsquo;t locked.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thread already joined&lt;/strong&gt; — joining a thread twice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 1: Deadlock&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex1 &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Mutex&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex2 &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Mutex&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;t1 &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex1&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; sleep &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex2&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize { } &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Waits for mutex2&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;t2 &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex2&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; sleep &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex1&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize { } &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Waits for mutex1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;t1&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;join &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ThreadError: deadlock detected&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 2: Join dead thread&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;thread &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;done&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;thread&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;join
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;thread&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;join &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ThreadError: dead thread&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 3: Unlock without lock&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Mutex&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;unlock &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ThreadError: unlocked from non-owner thread&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Cause 4: Double lock (not reentrant)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Mutex&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ThreadError: deadlock&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="solutions"&gt;Solutions&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-avoid-deadlock-with-lock-ordering"&gt;Fix 1: Avoid deadlock with lock ordering&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong — inconsistent lock order&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex1&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex2&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize { }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct — consistent lock order&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex1&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex2&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize { }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Always lock in the same order everywhere&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-thread-status-before-joining"&gt;Fix 2: Check thread status before joining&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;thread &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Thread&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new { &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;done&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;thread&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;join
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;thread&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;join &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# ThreadError&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; thread&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;status &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; thread&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;status&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;nil?
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Thread has already finished&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; thread&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;join
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-mutextry_lock-for-non-blocking"&gt;Fix 3: Use Mutex#try_lock for non-blocking&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Mutex&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong — may deadlock&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mutex&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Long operation&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Correct — try lock with timeout&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; mutex&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;try_lock
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;begin&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Operation&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;ensure&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; mutex&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;unlock
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; puts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Could not acquire lock&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-monitor-for-reentrant-locking"&gt;Fix 4: Use Monitor for reentrant locking&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;require &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;monitor&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;monitor &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;Monitor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;new
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# This works (Monitor is reentrant)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;monitor&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; monitor&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;synchronize &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Works fine&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="deadlock-lock"&gt;ThreadError: deadlock&lt;/a&gt; — deadlock specifically.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="fiber-error"&gt;FiberError&lt;/a&gt; — fiber-related errors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="memory-error"&gt;NoMemoryError&lt;/a&gt; — memory issues from threads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Ruby ThreadError: deadlock; recursive locking Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/deadlock-lock/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/ruby/deadlock-lock/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="threaderror-deadlock-recursive-locking-fix"&gt;ThreadError: deadlock; recursive locking Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;code&gt;ThreadError: deadlock; recursive locking&lt;/code&gt; is raised when a thread tries to lock a mutex that it already holds, or when multiple threads are waiting on each other&amp;rsquo;s locks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deadlock occurs when two or more threads are blocked forever, each waiting for the other to release a lock. Ruby detects this and raises &lt;code&gt;ThreadError&lt;/code&gt;. Recursive locking happens when a non-reentrant mutex is locked twice by the same thread.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>